pageContext.claim: “We're up 10,315 ballots were cast by individuals whose name and date of birth matches a Georgia resident who died in 2020 prior to the election and your wacky Secretary of State said, 'Two people. Two people.' Now, I don't know how many people are on that list, but it's a lot of people.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is citing claims made by Bryan Geels, a certified public accountant who owns a data analytics firm. Trump thinks he knows better than the state's top election official, who has access to the data and investigated the issue. But Georgia election officials say the figures are bogus.
